Class ThrustCurve

  • java.lang.Object
    • andrew_huber.umbc.cmsc455.hw1.io.ThrustCurve

  • public class ThrustCurve
extends java.lang.Object
    This stores a discrete thrust curve (as opposed to a continuous one). For more information on how the thrust curve is loaded, view the documentation for addValue(double, double)
    Author:
    andrew_huber

      • lowestSecond

      • highestSecond

      • step

        private double step
        The thrust curve loads in a list of key-value pairs. The keys are quantities measured in seconds, they are added in ascending order and each key is step more than the last value.

        For example, if the keys (quantities measured in seconds) are

        0.0, 0.1, 0.2, ...


        Then step is 0.1
